Note:
LINKED LIST - Singly and Doubly Linked Lists Tier 0 Primitive

This file implements both singly-linked and doubly-linked node-based
lists. Where a contiguous List would have O(n) head insertion cost,
linked lists give O(1) head/tail operations at the cost of cache
locality and a per-node memory overhead.

SinglyLinkedList structure (24 bytes):
  offset 0:  head node pointer (8 bytes) - 0 if empty
  offset 8:  tail node pointer (8 bytes) - 0 if empty, equal to head if one node
  offset 16: size (8 bytes)

Singly node (16 bytes):
  offset 0:  value (8 bytes)
  offset 8:  next node pointer (8 bytes)

DoublyLinkedList structure (24 bytes):
  offset 0:  head node pointer (8 bytes)
  offset 8:  tail node pointer (8 bytes)
  offset 16: size (8 bytes)

Doubly node (24 bytes):
  offset 0:  value (8 bytes)
  offset 8:  next node pointer (8 bytes)
  offset 16: prev node pointer (8 bytes)

Use cases:
- LRU cache backing (doubly: O(1) move-to-front)
- Streaming pipelines where each stage holds one node
- Free-list management for the slab allocator
- Symbol table chains
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CONSTANTS
Note: ============================================================================

Let SLIST_HEADER_SIZE be 24
Let SLIST_NODE_SIZE be 16
Let DLIST_HEADER_SIZE be 24
Let DLIST_NODE_SIZE be 24

Note: ============================================================================
Note: SINGLY-LINKED LIST
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Create an empty singly-linked list. No nodes are pre-allocated; the
header alone is 24 bytes and head/tail/size are all zero.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate 24 bytes, zero the three fields.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: 24 bytes.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "slist_create" returns Integer:
    Let list be proc allocate from Layout with SLIST_HEADER_SIZE
    If list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with list, 0, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with list, 8, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with list, 16, 0
    Return list
End Process

@Reasoning
Free every node, then the header. Node values are opaque words.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Walk the chain from head; save next, free current, advance. Stops at
null. Then free the header.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller-owned.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "slist_destroy" takes list as Integer returns Integer:
    If list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with list, 0
    While cur is not equal to 0:
        Let next be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 8
        proc deallocate from Layout with cur
        Set cur to next
    End While
    proc deallocate from Layout with list
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Element count accessor.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns size field at offset 16.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "slist_size" takes list as Integer returns Integer:
    If list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with list, 16
End Process

@Reasoning
Empty predicate.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns 1 if head pointer is 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "slist_is_empty" takes list as Integer returns Integer:
    If list is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let head be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with list, 0
    If head is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Push value at head of list. O(1) by definition of singly-linked lists.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1) Allocate new node, initialize value and next = current head.
2) Update list.head to new node.
3) If list was empty (tail was 0), set tail = new node too.
4) Increment size.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1) per insertion (16-byte node).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "slist_push_head" takes list as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    If list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let node be proc allocate from Layout with SLIST_NODE_SIZE
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let old_head be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with list, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, 0, value
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, 8, old_head
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with list, 0, node
    Let tail be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with list, 8
    If tail is equal to 0:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with list, 8, node
    End If
    Let size be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with list, 16
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with list, 16, size plus 1
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Push value at tail. O(1) thanks to the cached tail pointer.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1) Allocate new node, value set, next = 0.
2) If list empty, set head = tail = new node.
3) Else set old_tail.next = new node, then list.tail = new node.
4) Increment size.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "slist_push_tail" takes list as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    If list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let node be proc allocate from Layout with SLIST_NODE_SIZE
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, 0, value
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, 8, 0
    Let tail be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with list, 8
    If tail is equal to 0:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with list, 0, node
    Otherwise:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with tail, 8, node
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with list, 8, node
    Let size be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with list, 16
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with list, 16, size plus 1
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Pop value from head. O(1).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1) Empty check via head == 0.
2) Save value at head.
3) Advance list.head to head.next; if new head is 0, also clear tail.
4) Free old head node.
5) Decrement size, return value.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Empty returns 0.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "slist_pop_head" takes list as Integer returns Integer:
    If list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let head be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with list, 0
    If head is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let value be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with head, 0
    Let next be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with head, 8
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with list, 0, next
    If next is equal to 0:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with list, 8, 0
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with head
    Let size be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with list, 16
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with list, 16, size minus 1
    Return value
End Process

@Reasoning
Peek the head value without removing.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns 0 if empty, otherwise value field of head.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Empty returns 0.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "slist_peek_head" takes list as Integer returns Integer:
    If list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let head be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with list, 0
    If head is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with head, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Peek the tail value without removing.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns 0 if empty, otherwise value field of tail.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Empty returns 0.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "slist_peek_tail" takes list as Integer returns Integer:
    If list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let tail be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with list, 8
    If tail is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tail, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Linear search and remove the first node whose value equals target.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Walk with a (prev, cur) pair. When cur.value == target:
- If prev == 0 (head match), advance list.head to cur.next.
- Otherwise set prev.next = cur.next.
- If cur was tail, update list.tail to prev.
- Free cur and decrement size.
Returns 1 on success, 0 if not found.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Removes only first match; caller can call in a loop for all occurrences.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "slist_remove_value" takes list as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    If list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let prev be 0
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with list, 0
    While cur is not equal to 0:
        Let cv be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 0
        If cv is equal to value:
            Let next be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 8
            If prev is equal to 0:
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with list, 0, next
            Otherwise:
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with prev, 8, next
            End If
            Let tail be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with list, 8
            If cur is equal to tail:
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with list, 8, prev
            End If
            proc deallocate from Layout with cur
            Let size be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with list, 16
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with list, 16, size minus 1
            Return 1
        End If
        Set prev to cur
        Set cur to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 8
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Indexed accessor for traversal. O(n) for singly linked.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Walk 'index' nodes from head; return value of the node at that position.
Bounds-checked against size; returns 0 on out-of-range.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Bounds-checked.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "slist_get" takes list as Integer, index as Integer returns Integer:
    If list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If index is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let size be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with list, 16
    If index is greater than or equal to size:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with list, 0
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than index:
        Set cur to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 8
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: DOUBLY-LINKED LIST
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Create an empty doubly-linked list. Same overall shape as singly but
each node has a back-pointer that enables O(1) removal given a node
pointer and O(1) reverse traversal.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate 24 bytes, zero head/tail/size.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: 24 bytes.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "dlist_create" returns Integer:
    Let list be proc allocate from Layout with DLIST_HEADER_SIZE
    If list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with list, 0, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with list, 8, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with list, 16, 0
    Return list
End Process

@Reasoning
Free every node then the header.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Walk node chain; save next, free current, advance. Same loop shape as
singly's destroy; the prev pointers don't matter during destruction.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller-owned.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "dlist_destroy" takes list as Integer returns Integer:
    If list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with list, 0
    While cur is not equal to 0:
        Let next be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 8
        proc deallocate from Layout with cur
        Set cur to next
    End While
    proc deallocate from Layout with list
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Element count.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns size field at offset 16.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "dlist_size" takes list as Integer returns Integer:
    If list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with list, 16
End Process

@Reasoning
Empty predicate.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns 1 if head is 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "dlist_is_empty" takes list as Integer returns Integer:
    If list is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let head be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with list, 0
    If head is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Push at head. The prev/next fixup keeps the doubly-linked invariant.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1) Alloc node, value set, prev = 0, next = old head.
2) If old head non-zero, set old_head.prev = new node.
3) Set list.head = new node.
4) If tail was 0, also set list.tail = new node.
5) Increment size.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "dlist_push_head" takes list as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    If list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let node be proc allocate from Layout with DLIST_NODE_SIZE
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let old_head be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with list, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, 0, value
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, 8, old_head
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, 16, 0
    If old_head is not equal to 0:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with old_head, 16, node
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with list, 0, node
    Let tail be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with list, 8
    If tail is equal to 0:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with list, 8, node
    End If
    Let size be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with list, 16
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with list, 16, size plus 1
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Push at tail.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1) Alloc node, value set, next = 0, prev = old tail.
2) If old tail non-zero, set old_tail.next = new node.
3) Set list.tail = new node.
4) If head was 0, also set list.head = new node.
5) Increment size.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "dlist_push_tail" takes list as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    If list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let node be proc allocate from Layout with DLIST_NODE_SIZE
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let old_tail be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with list, 8
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, 0, value
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, 8, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, 16, old_tail
    If old_tail is not equal to 0:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with old_tail, 8, node
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with list, 8, node
    Let head be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with list, 0
    If head is equal to 0:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with list, 0, node
    End If
    Let size be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with list, 16
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with list, 16, size plus 1
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Pop from head. O(1) with prev-pointer fixup.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1) Empty check.
2) Save value, save next.
3) list.head = next; if next non-zero, next.prev = 0; else list.tail = 0.
4) Free head node.
5) Decrement size, return value.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Empty returns 0.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "dlist_pop_head" takes list as Integer returns Integer:
    If list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let head be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with list, 0
    If head is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let value be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with head, 0
    Let next be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with head, 8
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with list, 0, next
    If next is equal to 0:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with list, 8, 0
    Otherwise:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with next, 16, 0
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with head
    Let size be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with list, 16
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with list, 16, size minus 1
    Return value
End Process

@Reasoning
Pop from tail. O(1) thanks to the back-pointer.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1) Empty check.
2) Save value, save prev.
3) list.tail = prev; if prev non-zero, prev.next = 0; else list.head = 0.
4) Free old tail.
5) Decrement size, return value.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Empty returns 0.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "dlist_pop_tail" takes list as Integer returns Integer:
    If list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let tail be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with list, 8
    If tail is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let value be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tail, 0
    Let prev be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tail, 16
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with list, 8, prev
    If prev is equal to 0:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with list, 0, 0
    Otherwise:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with prev, 8, 0
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with tail
    Let size be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with list, 16
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with list, 16, size minus 1
    Return value
End Process

@Reasoning
Peek head and tail values.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Read value field of head or tail; empty returns 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Empty returns 0.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "dlist_peek_head" takes list as Integer returns Integer:
    If list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let head be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with list, 0
    If head is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with head, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Tail peek.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Reads value field of tail node.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Empty returns 0.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "dlist_peek_tail" takes list as Integer returns Integer:
    If list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let tail be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with list, 8
    If tail is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tail, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Remove a node given its pointer. The full prev/next surgery completes
in O(1) because both neighbors are immediately reachable.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1) Validate list and node.
2) Splice: prev.next = node.next (or list.head = node.next if prev == 0).
3) Splice: node.next.prev = node.prev (or list.tail = node.prev if
   node.next == 0).
4) Free the node, decrement size.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Caller must already hold the node pointer.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller-supplied node must belong to the list; verifying belonging is
caller's responsibility.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "dlist_remove_node" takes list as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    If list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let next be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, 8
    Let prev be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, 16
    If prev is equal to 0:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with list, 0, next
    Otherwise:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with prev, 8, next
    End If
    If next is equal to 0:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with list, 8, prev
    Otherwise:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with next, 16, prev
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with node
    Let size be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with list, 16
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with list, 16, size minus 1
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Find the first node with value equal to target and return its pointer,
0 if not found. Useful for LRU-style updates where the caller wants to
hold the node and call remove + push_head.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Walk from head, comparing value fields.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "dlist_find_node" takes list as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    If list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with list, 0
    While cur is not equal to 0:
        Let cv be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 0
        If cv is equal to value:
            Return cur
        End If
        Set cur to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 8
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Indexed get for compatibility with array-style access.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Walks forward 'index' nodes from head and returns value. Bounds-
checked.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Bounds-checked.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "dlist_get" takes list as Integer, index as Integer returns Integer:
    If list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If index is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let size be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with list, 16
    If index is greater than or equal to size:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with list, 0
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than index:
        Set cur to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 8
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 0
End Process
